 :tx/rationale "Create task: D4-5: Unix socket listener + accept loop. CONTEXT: Core daemon server — the main loop that accepts connections and dispatches requests. ADR-DAEMON-001 (Unix socket transport). APPROACH: (1) serve_daemon(braid_dir: &Path) -> Result<(), DaemonError> — the main daemon function. (2) Sequence: acquire_lock → open LiveStore → install_runtime_schema → bind UnixListener(.braid/daemon.sock) → install signal handlers (SIGTERM/SIGINT set AtomicBool) → accept loop. (3) Accept loop: check shutdown flag → accept connection (with 1s timeout for responsiveness) → set connection read timeout (30s) → read line → parse JSON-RPC → refresh_if_needed() → dispatch via handle_with_observation → write response → loop. (4) On shutdown: break accept loop → flush LiveStore → remove socket → release lock → exit 0. (5) Single-threaded: one request at a time (MVP). Connection queue depth = 16 (listen backlog). (6) Daemon-specific methods: daemon/shutdown (sets shutdown flag, responds 'ok'), daemon/status (returns PID, uptime, request_count, datom_count). (7) All other methods delegated to mcp::handle_tools_call (shared handlers from D4-3). ACCEPTANCE: (A) Daemon binds socket and accepts connections. (B) JSON-RPC requests through socket produce correct responses. (C) SIGTERM triggers clean shutdown. (D) Lock and socket files are cleaned up on shutdown. (E) Stale socket from previous crash is removed on startup. DEPENDS-ON: D4-1, D4-2, D4-3, D4-4. FILE: crates/braid/src/daemon.rs"
